12\n |archivedate = October 12, 2007\n}}\n* {{cite book\n |author=Thomas, Lowell\n |title=Old Gimlet Eye\n |location=New York\n |publisher=Farrar & Rinehart\n |year=1933\n |oclc=219896546\n |isbn=978-0-940328-01-3\n}}\n* {{cite web\n | accessdate=October 14, 2007\n |url=http://www.americanheritage.com/articles/magazine/ah/1987/7/1987_7_14.shtml\n |title=Ollie and Old Gimlet Eye\n |author=Ward, Geoffrey C\n |website=American Heritage Magazine\n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070913215113/http://www.americanheritage.com/articles/magazine/ah/1987/7/1987_7_14.shtml <!--Added by H3llBot-->\n |archivedate=September 13, 2007\n}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{Refbegin|colwidth=30em}}\n* {{cite book\n |last=Butler\n |first=Smedley D.\n |date=1935\n |title=War Is A Racket\n |url=https://ratical.org/ratville/CAH/warisaracket.html\n |location=New York\n |publisher=Round table Press, Inc.\n |oclc=3015073\n}}\n* {{cite journal\n |title=Butler, Smedley D\n |journal=Dictionary of American Biography, Supplements 1\u20132: To 1940 <!--|month=February (of what year?)-->\n}}\n* {{cite web\n |accessdate  = January 28, 2010\n |url         = http://www.mcbbutler.usmc.mil\n |title       = Camp Smedley Butler website\n |publisher   = [[United States Marine Corps]]\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20100212175652/http://www.mcbbutler.usmc.mil/\n |archivedate = February 12, 2010\n}}\n* {{cite book\n |author=Hoffman, Jon T.\n |editor=Muschett, James O. (Project)\n |others=Crumley, Beth L. (Illustration Editor), Charles J. Ziga (Design)\n |title=USMC: A Complete History\n |origyear=2002\n |edition=Beaux Arts\n |date=December 6, 2007\n |publisher=Hugh Lauter Levin Associates, Inc.\n |location=Printed in China\n |isbn=978-0-88363-617-6\n |pages=135, 146\u20139, 151, 154\u20135, 165\u20136, 216\u20137\n}}\n* {{cite web\n |url=http://www.wnyc.org/story/245301-marine-corps-general-who-called-war-racket/\n |title=The Marine Corps General Who Call